goAML-V2 · Executive Summary
goAML-V2 is an on-premise, AI-native Anti-Money Laundering intelligence platform built for a Financial Intelligence Unit (FIU) operating environment. It is designed to process high-volume transaction data in real time, automate investigative workflows, and generate regulatory-grade Suspicious Transaction Reports (STRs) — replacing manual, multi-hour analyst processes with sub-minute AI-assisted pipelines.
What it is
A full-stack AML platform deployed at /home/ze/dashboard-aml on a single high-performance server with 2× NVIDIA L40S GPUs (48 GB each). It integrates 8 locked NIM inference models, a graph-vector retrieval layer, document intelligence pipeline, BPMN workflow engine, and a React investigator UI — all within a self-contained, air-gapped-capable architecture.
What it does
The platform covers the full AML operations lifecycle: ingesting transactions, scoring risk in real time via XGBoost on Triton FIL, detecting suspicious patterns via Neo4j graph analysis, semantically retrieving relevant case history via Milvus, and drafting STR narratives using llama-3.3-70b-instruct. Document intake (KYC, bank statements) flows through Tika → OCR → PII redaction → structured field extraction before reaching storage. OpenSanctions provides sanctions and PEP screening.
