Key design decisions
The 70b model runs in FP8 precision with tensor parallelism across both GPUs — the only way to fit it on 96 GB total VRAM. The 8b model handles all latency-sensitive paths to keep the 70b reserved for quality-critical reasoning. The RAG pipeline (Milvus → reranker → LLM) ensures grounded, auditable outputs rather than hallucinated STR content. All PII is stripped before any data reaches a model or vector store.
Pending consideration
Swapping nv-embedqa-e5-v5 for llama-nemotron-embed-1b-v2 would add multilingual embedding coverage — relevant for Bangla and Arabic entity names in the BD operating context.
Strategic value
The platform compresses STR drafting from 4–8 hours to under 5 minutes, enables continuous transaction monitoring at scale, and keeps all sensitive financial data fully on-premise — at a fraction of the cost of commercial AML platforms ($500K–$3M/year equivalent).